fields.name: errata
fields.description: profile used in errata scans (currently same as the default profile)

fields.name: custom
fields.description: base profile for custom scans (without additional options, it only builds the package)

fields.name: cov-unstable
fields.description: experimental profile using the latest release of csmock

fields.name: errata-el5
fields.description: errata profile without ShellCheck, which is currently not available on el5

fields.name: errata-el8
fields.description: errata profile without Clang, which is currently not available on el8

fields.name: smatch
fields.description: experimental profile for running the smatch static analyzer

fields.name: gcc-unstable
fields.description: experimental profile using non-default GCC warning flags

fields.name: gcc-asan
fields.description: experimental profile that compiles with -fsanitize=address and runs %check

fields.name: gcc-lsan
fields.description: experimental profile that compiles with -fsanitize=leak and runs %check

fields.name: gcc-tsan
fields.description: experimental profile that compiles with -fsanitize=thread and runs %check

fields.name: gcc-ubsan
fields.description: experimental profile that compiles with -fsanitize=undefined and runs %check

fields.name: gcc-analyzer
fields.description: profile that runs `gcc -fanalyzer` in the background and captures its results (currently included in the default profile)

fields.name: mass-scan-el9
fields.description: profile for RHEL-9 mass scan (currently same as the default profile)

fields.name: valgrind
fields.description: experimental profile that makes binaries produced in %build run through valgrind in %check

fields.name: s390x-hack
fields.description: profile for emergency scanning of s390x packages in x86_64 buildroot
